The paper discusses a systems engineering process and proposes a principal-agent model to account for human behavior in systems design. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and decision-making, which are common topics in the cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also deals with systems and control, which are relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses simulations to study the optimal incentives, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
